.
#portioncontrol #healthyeating

node.text:
This is the last LIVE workout on IG for the next 4 weeks! I will be going live exclusively with my challenge members for the next 4 weeks! 🙋🏻‍♀️
.
40 sec work / 15 sec rest
Repeat for 2 rounds
.
1. Squat to press
2. Split squat R leg
3. Split squat L leg
4. Push ups
5. Mountain climbers
6. Dips
7. Heel elevated Glute bridges
8. Crunch + rev crunch
9. Shoulder taps
10. Burpees
.
#followalongworkout #homeworkout

node.text:
Link in bio to sign up @ainsley
.

What’s included:
🔹4 weeks of workouts (5 days per week - 2 upper body days, 2 lower body days and 1 HIIT cardio day)
🔹BONUS follow along ab challenge to add to your workouts every week
🔹Instructional videos for proper form
🔹LIVE HIIT follow along workout session every week
🔹Support community & access to my app
🔹Ability to connect Apple Watch, Fitbit and my fitness pal
🔹 Personal profile to track progress, photos, measurements, personal stats & workout log
🔹Daily gratitude & journaling
.
If you’ve done any of my other challenges this one will be via my app (both android and apple) and completely different!
.
#4weekchallenge #resistancebandschallenge

node.text:
3 x 6 min EMOM. EMOM = every minute on the minute you will be doing the following moves. Once the clock hits the next minute you stop what you’re doing and go back to the first move!
.
MIN 1-6
10 squat to press, 10 squat jumps, 10 mountain climbers
.
MIN 7-13
10 deadlifts, 10 rev lunges, 10 push-ups
.
MIN 14-20
10 lat raises, 10 sit ups, 10 burpees
.
#homeworkout #followalongworkout #EMOM #hiitworkout

40 sec work / 20 sec rest
.
1. Alt Rev Lunge to Squat Pulse
2. Alt Knee to Elbow Reach
3. Plank Squat in and out
4. Walk out to shoulder to knee taps
5. Rev Lunge w knee drive (20sec L / 20 sec R)
6. Arm call outs
7. Frog Pulses
8. Alt knee to leg crunch
9. Mountain Climber to shoulder taps
10. Side plank dips (20 sec each side)
**REPEAT**
.
#homeworkout #lowimpactworkout #followalongworkout

MIA ✈️ STL
.
IN A RUSH TRAVEL SNACK CHECKLIST! 🏃🏻‍♀️💨 🙋🏻‍♀️
.
90% of the time I’m running late when it comes to catching flights 🙃🤷🏻‍♀️ and with the airports getting busier and busier I’m sure most of you are as well! If you have time to wait in lines or sit have a seat for a meal that’s great - but I rather be prepared and have my travel snacks on hand!
.
✅ Protein on - the - go! These jerky sticks are a great no - mess option to get your protein in while waiting for your flight or when you get off the plane as a quick snack (these are NEWLY RELEASED and just came out TODAY - check my story for the direct link & stock up!)

✅Meal Replacement Bars - these are a little more dense with a combo of protein and carbs and great for having mid flight to hold you over until you get to your destination. (Check supp tab at link in bio for them)

✅ Dessert on - the - go! These @321glo brownies are the perfect craving killer!! Depending on my mood I’ll either have in flight or what I really like to do is save them for the hotel room as my late night snack before bed if I’m hungry 🤤
.
#travelsnacks #catchingflights #healthysnacks

node.text:
Drop some love 😍 for my client Megan and her transformation with me!
.
Megan was working late nights 5x / week and having trouble figuring out how to accommodate a healthy lifestyle to her current routine. I created a diet plan for megan that involved meals she could either pre-prep for the week or meals that didn’t require cooking that she could eat fairly quickly and easily at work. She trained at the gym some days and for days where she was too tired or couldn’t fit the trip in, I created an extra training plan for her that she could do at home with whatever she had available! After you sign up you fill out an open ended assessment form that allows me to get to know you, your lifestyle, your likes and dislikes, your struggles, fave foods, daily schedule and your goals! I then create a customized diet and training program that is specific to your needs and lifestyle!
.
This is after 7 months with me! People always wonder ‘how many months they will need’. That answer differs for everyone! There are a great deal of clients who reach their goals after just one month and are able to take what I teach and apply it successfully on their own. There are other clients who have more weight to lose or gain and others who reach their goals but continue with me because they enjoy having the leg work done for them and don’t want to think about what to eat or what workouts to do that week!
.
Clients spots are now open for next week! Send me a direct message for more info on getting started! 💪🏻

HIGH VOLUME LEG DAY 🦵🏼
.
This workout should take you about 40-50 mins - save it for your next gym session!
.
Superset 1: 3 Rounds
Leg press x 15 reps (push through heels)
RDL x 15 reps (push hips back & weight in heels)
.
Superset 2: 3 Rounds
Nordic Hamstring Curl x 10 sec hold and then 10 reps
Front Squat x 15 reps (keep your weight in heels)
.
Triset: 3 Rounds
Booty Builder / Hip Thrust x 15 reps
Calf Raises x 15 reps
Bodyweight Walking lunges down and back 15 paces each way
.
#legworkout #legday

node.text:
A B S ! ! !
.
Here are ways to level up (or level down) your core work! Instead of being discouraged by movements you can’t do, just adjust and modify and work your way up ☺️ YOU.GOT.THIS! 🔥
.
Slide 1. Reverse Plank
Beginners: Hold rev plank position as long as you can. If this bothers your wrists go ahead and opt for your knuckles.
Advanced: add single leg reverse crunches in reverse plank position keeping your core tight the entire time.
.
Slide 2: Russian twists
Beginners: Keep your feet on the floor for stability and rotate your torso touching the floor each time with your hands.
Advanced: Take your feet off the ground and use weights for added resistance while rotating your torso.
.
Slide 3: V ups
Beginners: Bend your knees
Advanced: Keep your legs as straight as possible
.
Slide 4: Side Plank
Beginners: Keep both feet on the ground and stagger them. If this is still too difficult you can opt for your knees but keep your hips high and don’t let them drop
Advanced: Take one leg off the floor into star position and also lift one arm to the sky
.
Slide 5: Boat Hold
Beginner: Use your arms to grab onto your thighs for support.
Advanced: Keep your core tight and your hands and legs in the air.
.
#abs #coreworkout #beginnerabs #advancedabs #abworkout

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Ainsley Rodriguez on August 01, 2021. May be an image of 1 person, beach and ocean.

node.text:
HAPPY SUNDAY! 🎉
Still in Chicago but developed some kind of infection under my nostril 3 days ago soooo an emergency dermatology appointment, antibiotics and 2 days later with half my face still swollen … I’ll wait on pics for a minute 🤣
.
Heading back home tonight and hopefully my face is back to normal too lollll. Until next time chi-town!
.
Wearing @findyoursalt_ Aria top and Demi bottom in Fiery Red! Link in bio to shop #swimwear

node.text:
20 min F U L L  BODY BURN 🔥 !
.
This workout only takes 20 mins so you’ll need all the energy you can get! Grab your @celsiusofficial and a pair of dumbbells and LETS GO!
.
Aim for 10-15 reps each move and repeat as a circuit for 4 rounds
.
#fullbodyworkout #celsiuslivefit #celsiusbrandpartner

node.text:
Health > all the BS out there.
.
I got hooked on ‘numbers’ and fad diets at a very young age. I was obsessed. I was chasing this image of ‘perfect’ that I thought would solve all my troubles. It didn’t.
.
Why don’t I count macros or calories? Because when I did I wasn’t listening to my body. I wasn’t paying attention to what foods were making me bloated and uncomfortable. I was just simply eating to numbers. I mistook bloat for ‘fat’. I ate after I was full and I refrained from eating even when I was hungry. I restricted food. I deprived myself. I binged. I jumped from fad diet to fad diet thinking ‘this time it will be different’. It wasn’t.
-
I thought I had tried everything BUT the one thing I hadn’t tried was being HEALTHY. When I started to TRULY care about my health and not my waist to bum ratio is when my whole world changed. My relationship with myself changed...Inside AND OUT!
-
I speak to you from experience when I say I know EXACTLY what it’s like to suffer with body image and digestive issues and think you’re doing everything right while tossing your hands up in frustration at not seeing results. I can confidently tell you that it starts with changing your habits and letting go of the obsession. It starts with small changes daily that equate to bigger, more sustainable and long term results later 🙏🏼
.
#lifestylechanges #health

❓Struggling with push-ups? 💡Try this!
.
Grab a resistance band (the thicker the more help you’ll have)
Loop it around a high bar and bring it around your waist
.
The resistance band will help you come up and you can go decreasing the resistance as you get better until you no longer need it! 💪🏻
.
#pushups #pushuphack #fitnesshack

node.text:
45lbs and 10 PANT SIZES DOWN with my client Cassandra after 4.5 months with me!! 🎉 Drop some love and support for her ! ❤️👇🏻
.
A busy mom working full time who like many of us, found it difficult to exercise on limited time! We made some adjustments to her schedule, had her training from home with limited equipment and still managed to make this journey enjoyable and CONSISTENT!! I am soooo PROUD of this woman for sticking with it and I can’t wait to see more results to come!!
.
The beauty of truly customized and personalized programs is that I literally learn pretty much everything about your lifestyle, previous struggles, limitations, time constraints etc and build fitness to work around it - not the other way around! It’s like having a personal trainer and coach at your fingertips at all times ☺️
.
Now accepting clients for next week! Send me a message with your email for more info on getting started!
.
*You now have the option to pay in 4 installments bi-weekly*
.
#weightlossjourney

THE BEST Refreshing Summer Salad Recipe 🤤 (Sound On 🔈for recipe)
.
So simple and the combo is OUT.OF.CONTROL. Save for parties, family dinners or just for yourself 🤷🏻‍♀️
.
Ingredients:
2 cups of watermelon
1 c cucumber
1/4c red onion
Fresh cilantro or basil to taste
1/2 lemon
1/2 lime
Drizzle of honey
Crack of sea salt
Sprinkle of Feta or Goat cheese
.
Directions:
Mix it all together and enjoy!!
.
#summersalad #healthyrecipes #saladrecipe #healthyrecipe
